{"lemma":"عَبْرَةٌ","slug":"عَبْرَةٌ","root":"ع.ب.ر","root_slug":"ع-ب-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ب-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَبْرَةٌ","root":"عبر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":6},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27832"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"example, lesson, warning","examples":[{"text":"لَقَدْ كَانَ فِي قَصَصِهِمْ عِبْرَةٌ لِأُولِي الْأَلْبَابِ","english":"There is a lesson in the stories of such people for those who understand."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a tear before it overflows, a sobbing, the first sign of weeping","examples":[{"text":"فَفَاضَت دُمُوعُ الْجَحْمَتَيْنِ بِعَبْرَةٍ … عَلَى الزُبِّ حَتَّى الزُبِّ فِي المَاءِ غَامِس","english":"And the tears of the two eyes overflowed without sobbing … over the beard, until the beard was dipping into water"},{"text":"أسندتْ رأسها إلى صدري وسالت عبراتها.","english":"She leant her head on my chest where slight tears flew."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ع ب ر (ʕ b r). Compare to عَبْر (ʕabr, “crossing”)."},"ipa":["/ʕib.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27832","headword_ar":"عَبْرَةٌ","root":"Ebr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EibaArapN","text_ar":"عِبَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tear:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tear before it overflows:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sobbing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reiteration"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sound"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of weeping in the bosom:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an overflowing of tears without the sound of weeping:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a flowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an oozing, of tears:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grief without weeping:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabaraAtN","text_ar":"عَبَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabarN","text_ar":"عَبَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the O, [but this, if correct, is a quasi-pl. n.,]) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EibarN","text_ar":"عِبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Thus in copies of the K.) Of the first meaning, the following is an ex.:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waA_in~a $ifaAy^iY EaborapN lawo safaHotuhaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And verily my cure would be a tear if I shed it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and of the last, the following is an ex.:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"laka maA A^abokiY walaA Eaborapa biY"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some relate it,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wlA Ebrp liY","text_ar":"ولا عبرة لِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"For thy sake I weep, but there is grief in me for myself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says As: (TA:) or in this saying, which is a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA","text_ar":"ما"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be redundant, or it may be what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maSodariy~ap","text_ar":"مَصْدَرِيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"For thee I weep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for thee is my weeping, I"},{"kind":"text","text":"[myself]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no need of weeping."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Meyd.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","A","K","S","O"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}